# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for Pensees
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Repo is currently greenfield (README-only). Sections below are intentionally
# broad so the ignore set stays useful as the codebase grows. Prune unused
# language sections later once the tech stack solidifies.
#
# IMPORTANT: The DevolaFlow agent workspace and compiled outputs are ignored
# wholesale here (per W1.T2 acceptance criteria). Do NOT re-introduce the
# legacy `.local/*` whitelist (with `!.local/memory/specs/**` negations) that
# earlier scaffold versions emitted — that defeats the "no untracked .local
# noise" goal the operator chose under commit-strategy option C.
# =============================================================================

# DevolaFlow agent workspace (internal state — never commit)
# Everything under .local/ is per-agent scratch / task / memory / handoff
# state. It must stay local; do not whitelist subpaths. The sibling .rules/
# directory holds project source-of-truth rule files (*.mdc, compile-config.
# yaml) and IS tracked; only the compile cache (.compile-hashes.json) is
# ignored.
.local/

# DevolaFlow compiled outputs (regenerated by devola-init / rule compiler)
# These are derived from .rules/*.mdc sources. Re-running the compiler
# reproduces them exactly, so they should not pollute git history.
/AGENTS.md
.rules/.compile-hashes.json

# =============================================================================
# Multi-agent / multi-IDE tooling state (per-machine, per-session — never share)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each editor / agent CLI writes its own scratch directory at the repo root:
# skill caches, command history, rule snapshots, plan files, worker logs,
# etc. They are regenerated by upstream tooling on demand and pollute
# `git status` wholesale on a fresh checkout. None of them are
# source-of-truth files. Source-of-truth surfaces stay tracked:
# `.rules/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `skill/**`, `docs/**`, `site/**`,
# `tests/**`, `README.md`, `LICENSE`, `install.sh`, `get.sh`, `.gitignore`.
# Note: `.cursor/` here subsumes the legacy `.cursor/rules/` and
# `.cursor/plans/` entries — the broader pattern is correct and the
# narrow ones are deliberately dropped to avoid confusion.
# =============================================================================
.agent/
.agent-worker-logs/
.claude/
.clinerules/
.codebuddy/
.codex/
.continue/
.cursor/
.gemini/
.kiro/
.opencode/
.qoder/
.roo/
.trae/
.windsurf/

# Per-tool version pins / single-file rule bundles dropped at the repo root
# by `devola-init` / `popola init` / similar agent installers. These mirror
# `.rules/*.mdc` at install time and are reproduced on update.
.devola-flow-version
.popola-loom-version
.windsurfrules

# GitHub-side agent helpers — keep `.github/workflows/**` tracked, but
# treat helper files / prompt directories dropped by IDEs and agents as
# machine-local state.
.github/.popola-loom-version
.github/copilot-instructions.md
.github/prompts/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
# If the team later wants to share editor settings, un-ignore specific files
# here (example):
# !.vscode/settings.json
# !.vscode/extensions.json
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Language-agnostic build artifacts
# Trim the sections below once the project's actual stack is known.

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.tox/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
dist/
build/
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# --- Node / JS / TS ---
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log
pnpm-debug.log*
.next/
.nuxt/
.turbo/
.parcel-cache/
.cache/

# --- Rust ---
target/
Cargo.lock.bak

# --- Go ---
vendor/
*.test
*.out

# --- Java / JVM ---
*.class
*.jar

# Logs / temp / env
*.log
logs/
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.tmp
*.temp
coverage/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/

# =============================================================================
# Secrets / credentials (machine-local — NEVER commit)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Defense-in-depth on top of the dotenv block above: catch the other
# common shapes a leak takes — SSH / signing keys, certificate bundles,
# cloud-provider service-account JSON, and generic `secrets/` directories.
# Public templates are explicitly un-ignored via negation so a repo
# template like `.env.example` stays trackable when one is later added.
# =============================================================================
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.sample
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.cer
*.keystore
*.jks
id_rsa
id_rsa.*
id_dsa
id_dsa.*
id_ecdsa
id_ecdsa.*
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.*
credentials.json
service-account*.json
secrets.yaml
secrets.yml
.secrets/
.local-secrets/
.direnv/

tests/fixtures/v032/*/review.md
